The White House Press Secretary released a statement applauding the verdict of the Special Court for Sierra Leone in the case of Charles Taylor. Taylor was convicted of war crimes and crimes against humanity during Sierra Leone's civil war in the 1990s. The statement emphasizes the importance of accountability and sending a message to war criminals. It also highlights the progress made by Sierra Leone and Liberia in transitioning beyond conflict and building democratic institutions. The statement concludes with President Obama's belief that strong institutions are needed for peace and prosperity in Africa.